{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T09:18:10.585Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Agent run dashboards and anomaly detection"},{"type":"text","text":" in Agent Observability at Scale are the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"visual control plane"},{"type":"text","text":" and the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"automated guardrails"},{"type":"text","text":" for a distributed multi-agent swarm. Dashboards give you real-time, session-level visibility into prompts, tool calls, latency percentiles, token usage, and costs; anomaly detection applies statistical or ML-based models to that telemetry to automatically surface unusual patterns (e.g., infinite loops, token escalation, repeated prompts, latency spikes, or sudden cost increases) before they become production failures.[]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Agent run dashboards"},{"type":"text","text":" are interactive UIs that show:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Per-run metrics"},{"type":"text","text":": latency, tokens, cost, model, status."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Aggregated metrics"},{"type":"text","text":": p50/p95/p99 latency, total cost, failure rate."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tool analytics"},{"type":"text","text":": which tools are most invoked, error rates, execution times."}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Event streams"},{"type":"text","text":": live model calls, tool execut